    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a suborder containing the families Cyclopedidae and Myrmecophagidae, comprising four species of quadruped mammals having elongated skulls and tubular muzzles, with long, thread-like viscous tongues used to catch and consume small insects such as ants and termites.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
